---
import Presentation from "../../../components/Presentation.astro";
import Divider from "../../../components/ui/Divider.astro";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";

//#region CodeSnippets
const Figure1 = `i = 0

while i < 5:
    print(i)
    i = i + 1`;
const Figure2 = `for i in range(5):
    print(i)`;
const Figure3 = `0
1
2
3
4`;
const Figure4 = `for i in range(1, 11):
    print(i)`;
const Figure5 = `for i in range(10, 0, -1):
    print(i)`;
const Task1 = `number = int(input("Choose a number: "))
count = int(input("List how many multiples of the number? "))

total = number  # Tracks the current multiple

for i in range(count):
    print(total)
    total = total + number

input("Press enter to continue...")
`;
const Task2 = `number = int(input("Choose a number: "))
count = int(input("List how many multiples of the number? "))

total = number  # Tracks the current multiple

for i in range(count):
    print(total, end=" ")
    total = total + number

print()
input("Press enter to continue...")
`;
const SampleOutput = `Choose a number: 3
List how many multiples of the number? 5
3 6 9 12 15
Press enter to continue...`;
//#endregion
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/foce/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.16: For Loops</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.16</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">For Loops</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>The for Loop</p>
              <p>range()</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Counting a Known Number of Times</h2>
              <p>
                When you already know how many times to repeat something,
                a <code>while</code> loop needs some bookkeeping.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>The for Loop</h2>
              <p>
                A <b class="text-sn-theme">for</b> loop does that counting
                for you.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">Same result as the <code>while</code> version &mdash; no counter variable to manage yourself.</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>The for Loop</h2>
              <Code code={Figure3} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>range()</h2>
              <p>
                <code>range(5)</code> counts <code>0</code> through
                <code>4</code> &mdash; 5 numbers, starting at 0.
                <code>range(start, stop)</code> lets you pick both ends.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure4} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">Counts 1 through 10.</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Counting Backwards</h2>
              <p>A third number in <code>range()</code> sets the step &mdash; negative counts down.</p>
              <Code code={Figure5} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">Counts 10 down to 1.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Writing a <code>for</code> loop with <code>range()</code></li>
                <li>Choosing between <code>range(n)</code> and <code>range(start, stop)</code></li>
                <li>Printing on the same line with <code>end=" "</code></li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>for Loop</dt>
                  <dd>Repeats its block once for each value in a sequence.</dd>
                  <dt>range()</dt>
                  <dd>Generates a sequence of numbers for a <code>for</code> loop to count through.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new Python script named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-16-for-loops.py</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Counting Multiples</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask for a number and a count, then print that many multiples of it, one per line.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-16-for-loops.py" mark="6-8" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Display on One Line</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Change the loop to print the multiples on a single line, separated by spaces.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-16-for-loops.py" mark="7,10" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>What does <code>range(count)</code> actually produce, and what does the loop use it for if <code>i</code> is never printed?</li>
            <li>Why doesn't a <code>for</code> loop need you to write your own counter variable and increment it, the way a <code>while</code> loop does?</li>
            <li>What does <code>end=" "</code> change about how <code>print()</code> behaves?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
